      <title>Hammer and Robe Itemization in DoDH</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=clericbalance&amp;message.id=8636#M8636</link>
      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;Okay so I've read&amp;nbsp;Zajeer would give some thought to future hammer itemization, and that Saroc mentioned the robes would be in some itemization somehow. So here are my concerns, the Hammer itemization if it's going to be similar to PoP and have no dps increase is somewhat of a downer. Honestly, I think that an increase in dps between an established cleric and a newer cleric should be different beyond the AA. That being especially the high end hammers compared to the lower end hammers. &lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;From what I've read the future robe stance is it won't have as high AC, which is fine because a robe is well a robe. The itemization I'd like to see is something that is from mid end(group drop)-&amp;gt;end game. I just think that robes are really cool, and "back in the day" added some seperation to clerics.&amp;nbsp;I also remember this small unused quest npc:&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;A href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/quest.html?quest=2994" target=_blank&gt;http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/quest.html?quest=2994&lt;/A&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;It's meant to turn robes into tunics. I think it would be cool for both int casters, monks, and clerics to be able to convert their robes into tunics or vica verca. Perhaps even add something to the quest to alter the tunics into robes again by having to fetch more cloth. Also, it would allow itemization for dwarves and halflings by giving them more style options (at the cost of AC). &lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Also, wearing a robe would rock because I&amp;nbsp;can look cool and&amp;nbsp;just say I'm a necromancer to avoid buff beggers &amp;nbsp;:smileywink:.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
